    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.939/199: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Swatow</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your October 20, noon, to Peiping.<note n="19" xml:id="d459fn19">Not
                        printed.</note> A Japanese Embassy statement to the press of October 23<note
                        n="19" xml:id="d459fn20">Not printed.</note> gives details of the second
                    linen shipment from Swatow and continues</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The exporters thus benefited donated 175,000 Chinese dollars to the local
                        Welfare Committee as an expression of their appreciation of the efforts of
                        the Japanese authorities in affording the export facilities. The donation
                        will be used for the general welfare and for the maintenance of peace and
                        order in the locality. Furthermore, the Japanese authorities there promised
                        to consider facilitating future transportation and importation of
                        materials.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>The Department would appreciate receiving your comment on this statement and any
                    information discreetly obtainable in regard to the “donation”.</p>
                <p>Sent to Swatow. Repeated to Peiping and Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
